# Line-ending and whitespace hygiene.
#
# thinlet.dtd is preserved byte-verbatim from the 2005 archive. Marking it
# `binary` bypasses any line-ending normalization or text diffing on
# checkout/checkin, guaranteeing the bytes never change (see DECISIONS.md).

* text=auto eol=lf

*.java   text eol=lf
*.xml    text eol=lf
*.html   text eol=lf
*.css    text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.yml    text eol=lf
*.yaml   text eol=lf
*.properties text eol=lf
*.md     text eol=lf

# Windows batch scripts need CRLF (Maven wrapper mvnw.cmd).
*.cmd    text eol=crlf
*.bat    text eol=crlf

# DTD: byte-verbatim, never rewritten.
*.dtd    binary

# Deliberate non-UTF-8 2005 artifact: the i18n demo is ISO-8859-2 (declared in
# its XML prolog). Thinlet's parser reads XML with the platform-default charset,
# so these bytes are behavior-relevant test input — preserve them verbatim, no
# EOL or encoding normalization. See project-docs/ENCODING-INVENTORY.md, DECISIONS.md
# D9/D12/D26.
thinlet-core/src/test/resources/corpus/drafts/internationalization.xml -text
thinlet-drafts/src/main/resources/thinlet/drafts/internationalization.xml -text

# Binary assets shipped with the original docs.
*.png    binary
*.ico    binary
*.jar    binary

# The 2005 icon GIFs, extracted byte-verbatim from the archive demo/draft jars
# (see project-docs/ICON-PROVENANCE.md, DECISIONS.md D54). Marking them `binary`
# bypasses EOL normalization and text diffing so the bytes are never rewritten —
# the golden traces depend on their exact intrinsic dimensions.
*.gif    binary
